## Visualisations

| # | Chart | Type | Key Interaction |
|---|-------|------|-----------------|
| 1 | Metric Cards | KPI cards | Updates on all filter changes |
| 2 | Annual Crashes by Severity | Stacked bar |Click bar → cross-filter all charts|
| 3 | Crash Density: Hour × Day | Heatmap | Hover for tooltip |
| 4 | Speed Zone vs. Fatality Rate | Bubble/scatter | Hover for stats |
| 5 | Crashes by Age Group | Donut | Click → filter funnel chart |
| 6 | Severity Funnel | Custom funnel | Reacts to donut selection |
| 7 | Crash Volume by Vehicle Type | Multi-line | Click legend to toggle series |

### Bidirectional Interactions
- **Stacked Bar ↔ All Charts**: clicking a year bar filters every other chart; resetting the bar restores all charts.
- **Donut ↔ Funnel**: clicking an age segment in the donut filters the funnel chart; clicking again resets it.

---

## Application Architecture (`scripts/main.js`)

```
loadData()               ← async: loads 3 CSVs, calls initFilters() + updateAll()
  ├── initFilters()      ← attaches event listeners to all filter controls
  ├── applyFilters()     ← returns filtered accident array from global state
  ├── applyPersonFilter()← joins persons to filtered accidents
  ├── applyVehicleFilter()← joins vehicles to filtered accidents
  └── updateAll()        ← calls all 7 draw functions with fresh filtered data
        ├── drawMetricCards()
        ├── drawStackedBar()
        ├── drawHeatmap()
        ├── drawScatter()
        ├── drawDonut()
        ├── drawFunnel()
        └── drawLine()
```

Each `draw*()` function:
- Accepts pre-filtered data as a parameter
- Clears its SVG and re-renders with D3 enter/update/exit pattern
- Uses CSS transitions + D3 transitions for animations
- Emits events or mutates `state.*` for cross-chart interactions

---

## Technology Stack

- **D3.js v7** — all data visualisations
- **Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS** — no frameworks
- **Python + pandas** — data preprocessing only (not part of the web app)

